{
  "stem": "21482.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And my father was able to get a permit for my mother and myself.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I was 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But they changed my birth certificate to make me 12.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And my father was able to obtain a permit for some of his brothers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Some of his brothers were working.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Some-- a couple of his brothers were-- and his father were house painters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So the Germans needed them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My, my father-- my mother's brothers, who-- they could not get a permit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they had to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I think that they were sent to Tarnow, to another-- outside of Cracow.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And my mother's sister and her husband with the two little girls, my cousins Rita and Jenny, they could not remain.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They had to leave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "My grandparents were able to stay.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I am sure my father was able to arrange it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And my mother's younger sister stayed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "In the building where I lived, a lot of my neighbors could not stay.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And they had to relocate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They had to be relocated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So-- and then of course, the Germans started the Aktions.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they started to grab people off the street, people from work.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And people were being taken away every day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw-- I saw it happening from far away a couple of times where I was on a street.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had to work.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We all had to work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And most of the time, my father was somehow able to arrange for me not to have to work on the streets, to clean the streets, to sweep the street.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the few times that he couldn't, and I was sweeping the streets, cleaning the streets of manure, I saw the Germans rounding up the Hasidic Jews on the old part of town in Cracow, Kazimierz.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
